President Obama issued a statement on Easter weekend, expressing his and Michelle's participation in the celebration. He emphasized the significance of Good Friday and the Resurrection of Jesus Christ, acknowledging the sacrifice and triumph associated with these events. The President reflected on the presence of God during times of suffering and celebration, expressing gratitude for the blessings in their lives. He concluded by renewing their commitment to follow Christ's example by loving God and their neighbors. The President extended well wishes to all who celebrate Easter.